@NODE "Honey" "Look! They are searchin' for new membas!"


                  /·/  ·==========================·  /·/

            Honey will soon celebrate her one year anniversary.

              So, now we are looking for more members again.
 We sent out a textfile for apx. 10 months ago and we've been growing since.

                  /·/  ·==========================·  /·/




                     «« [ information - divisions ] »»


   Honey is a group with several divisions. we fill up most subjects of the
   today amiga-scene. the members have some years of experience, so we know
   what we're doing here.



    >>  Demo-Division.

   The demo-division is mostly from sweden and we have very nice contact
   in the group. we work much independent from the trader & board-division,
   while many of us don't have modems and can't contact on the net. though,
   we try to show the rest of the group what we've done and what we're
   working on. we do also take inspiration and ideas from everybody in the
   group ofcourse.

     coders:   beverage      [swe]     graphicians:   laz           [swe]
               b.e.o.l       [aus]                    pad           [swe]
               hence         [swe]                    pulse         [swe]
               tito          [swe]

  musicians:   flea          [swe]         swapper:   rooster       [swe]
               qen           [swe]

   we are looking for coders & graphicians. but also other members who
   feels like they've something to give us. contact.



    >>  Utility-Division.

   This is a small division which we hope will grow. we are talking Utilities.
   it has not as much pressure as the demo-division and the members are
   releasing their work when they have their productions ready. it's not any
   specific utilities, and there is some members in the demo-division which
   releases some utilities now and then too. everything from /x-doors,
   cli-commands and other workbench - a'like - files.

                  utilitity-coders:   greedysnitch  [swe]
                                      gann          [swe]
                                      distler       [swe]

   we are looking for active utility-coders which have much ideas and
   inspiration for future amiga-productions.



    >> Trader & Boards-Division.

   What do we have here? this is a quite big part of honey. though, it's
   much to support our boards, and to spread internal files, but also to get
   our productions and name spread around the globe ofcourse. we also have an
   internal trader-chart which we got a counter-utility for very recently.
   that will be a big step in this division.

    sysops:   distler       [swe]      traders:   ruskis & storm  [swe]
              diablo        [hol]                 black line      [swe]
              black beard   [us!]                 mozart          [swe]
              h2o           [ger]                 marduk          [swe]
              psycho        [aus]                 diz'nee         [swe]
              baffle        [nor]                 the cat killer  [swe]
              webster       [den]                 black panther   [arg]
              ziz           [swe]                 kurgan          [oz!]
              stylewars     [ger]                 madsen          [nor]
                                                  numen           [nor]
    boards:   the slammer           [whq] [swe]   drakar          [nz!]
              the payoff            [ehq] [hol]   nup             [fin]
              maximum anarchy       [shq] [swe]
              electronic confusion  [dhq] [den]
              bumble bee land       [nhq] [nor]
              raveland              [ghq] [ger]
              shining chrome        [ahq] [aus]
              apocalypse now        [ghq] [ger]
              masturbation station  [uhq] [us!]

   we are looking for quality traders. especially in denmark, but also in
   us and the rest of europe.



    >> Ascii-Division. Atre.

   Atre come up recently and is now our Ascii-Division. we still have some
   members in honey who is ascii-artists anyway, who has not joined atre.
   all news within atre is written in the internal texts in honey. and they
   are also a part of our group and is looked at as honey-members from fellow
   honey's. there will come info about atre to the boards. you'll hear from
   us.

    atre:   drakar       [nz!]        ascii-artists:   dartagnan    [oz!]
            gozz         [swe]                         scarface     [hol]
            nup          [fin]                         stylewars    [ger]
            homicide     [nz!]
            zack         [hol]

   we are looking for  high  quality ascii-artists.



                  /·/  ·==========================·  /·/

        Internal news is released quite often and gives all members
    the news what's up in the divisions, who joins, who leaves, who did
                      what and who didn't do nothin'.

                  /·/  ·==========================·  /·/



